verses.verse: יְהוָ֣ה <WH3068> Yah-weh The LORD מָלָךְ֮ <WH4427> ma-loCh reigneth גֵּא֪וּת <WH1348> ge-'Ut with majesty לָ֫בֵ֥שׁ <WH3847> la-Vesh he is clothed לָבֵ֣שׁ <WH3847> la-Vesh is clothed יְ֭הוָה <WH3068> Yah-weh the LORD עֹ֣ז <WH5797> 'oz with strength הִתְאַזָּ֑ר <WH247> hit-'az-Zar; [wherewith] he hath girded אַף־ <WH637> 'af- Indeed תִּכּ֥וֹן <WH3559> tik-Kon also is stablished תֵּ֝בֵ֗ל <WH8398> te-Vel, himself the world בַּל־ <WH1077> bal- lest תִּמּֽוֹט׃ <WH4131> tim-Mot. that it cannot be moved

נָכ֣וֹן <WH3559> na-Chon [is] established כִּסְאֲךָ֣ <WH3678> kis-'a-Cha Thy throne מֵאָ֑ז <WH227> me-'Az; of old מֵֽעוֹלָ֣ם <WH5769> me-'o-Lam thou [art] from everlasting אָֽתָּה׃ <WH859> 'At-tah. you

נָשְׂא֤וּ <WH5375> na-se-'U have lifted up נְהָר֨וֹת׀ <WH5104> ne-ha-Rot The floods יְֽהוָ֗ה <WH3068> Yah-weh O LORD נָשְׂא֣וּ <WH5375> na-se-'U have lifted up נְהָר֣וֹת <WH5104> ne-ha-Rot the floods קוֹלָ֑ם <WH6963> ko-Lam; their voice יִשְׂא֖וּ <WH5375> yis-'U lift up נְהָר֣וֹת <WH5104> ne-ha-Rot the floods דָּכְיָֽם׃ <WH1796> da-che-Yam. their waves

מִקֹּל֨וֹת׀ <WH6963> mik-ko-Lot than the noise מַ֤יִם <WH4325> Ma-yim waters רַבִּ֗ים <WH7227> rab-Bim, of many אַדִּירִ֣ים <WH117> 'ad-di-Rim [is] mightier מִשְׁבְּרֵי־ <WH4867> mish-be-rei- waves יָ֑ם <WH3220> Yam; of the sea אַדִּ֖יר <WH117> 'ad-Dir [yea than] the mighty בַּמָּר֣וֹם <WH4791> bam-ma-Rom on high יְהוָֽה׃ <WH3068> Yah-weh. The LORD

עֵֽדֹתֶ֨יךָ׀ <WH5713> 'e-do-Tei-cha Thy testimonies נֶאֶמְנ֬וּ <WH539> ne-'em-Nu sure מְאֹ֗ד <WH3966> me-'Od, are very לְבֵיתְךָ֥ <WH1004> le-vei-te-Cha thine house נַאֲוָה־ <WH4998> na-'a-vah- becometh קֹ֑דֶשׁ <WH6944> Ko-desh; holiness יְ֝הוָ֗ה <WH3068> Yah-weh O LORD לְאֹ֣רֶךְ <WH753> le-'O-rech forever יָמִֽים׃ <WH3117> ya-Mim. age
